COPS and authorities have warned people that It is
illegal to leave your bank card with a money-lender in exchange for a loan. This is after a man believed to be a loan shark was
arrested after he was found in possession of bank cards and Identity documents. An intelligence driven operation between the Hawks’
Serious Commercial Crime Investigation Unit and National Credit Regulator resulted
in the arrest of the alleged loan shark aged 22. He was arrested  for Contravention of Sec 133 (1) (a) of the
National Credit Act 34 of 2005. Hawks spokesperson Captain Matimba Maluleke  said four South Africa Social Security Agency
(SASSA) cards, 45 identity documents, 16 bank cards and registers were seized
when the team pounced on the suspect  at
a local shop in Bela-Bela.